-- Brazil’s Sugar Producers Seen Selling 2014 Crop on Weaker Real
-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 2013-06-03T10:34:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-03/brazil-s-sugar-producers-seen-selling-2014-crop-on-weaker-real.html
Producers took advantage of a
weakening local currency last wk to sell some of their 2014 crop
in the futures market, Lausanne, Switzerland-based researcher
Kingsman SA says in report e-mailed today.
* “All the 2014 futures months made new contract lows,” says
Kingsman, a unit of  McGraw-Hill Financial Inc. (MHFI) ’s Platts
* Brazil’s real fell to a four-year low on May 31
* NOTE: Brazil is the world’s top sugar producer  To contact the reporter on this story:
